                   functions is mostly displaced, in respect to
                   LambdaCDM, in the opposite way of uncoupled dynamical
                   DE. This is an aspect of the basic underlying result,
                   that even a little DM-DE coupling induces relevant
                   modifications in the non-linear evolution. Therefore,
                   without causing great shifts in linear astrophysical
                   observables, the DM-baryon segregation induced by the
                   coupling can have an impact on a number of
                   cosmological problems, it e.g., galaxy satellite
                   abundance, spiral disk formation, apparent baryon
                   shortage, entropy input in clusters, etc..},
